ed from the final summary payload before posting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure appears at module handoff across collection/filtering/serialization stages. Concrete Unit-miss proof: dedup/filter stage accidentally removes findings with same path but different lines; individual functions pass unit tests, end-to-end payload count mismatches. Integration-brake checks: no mandatory real OS/network/subprocess, no model-output correctness dependency, no multi-agentic sequence. Rejected higher level (System) because behavior text focuses on pre-post payload completeness, which can be verified in-process.","test_description":"Run the inline-findings-to-summary assembly pipeline with multi-file/multi-line fixtures and assert final summary payload contains a 1:1 set of all inline findings.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"The automation sequence (read diff, post inline comments, post summary) succeeds for a real pull request when provided a fixed precomputed finding set.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Requires real GitHub API/network behavior across sequential calls. Concrete Integration-miss proof: local mocks won’t reproduce real API ordering/rate-limit/validation behavior that can fail summary posting after inline comments. Rejected higher level (Agentic) because findings are fixed precomputed, so correctness does not depend on live model decisions.","test_description":"Run against a real PR using a fixed findings fixture; verify diff retrieval, successful inline comment creation, and successful top-level summary post in one uninterrupted run.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.85,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"The full live run with model-generated findings (read diff, analyze